You can invert the `! seesWater(AHEAD)` condition. Then you can move the code in its `else` clause to its `if` clause:

```
if (! seesWater(LEFT))
{
    turn(LEFT);
}
else if (seesWater(AHEAD)) 
{
    if (! seesWater(RIGHT))
    {
        turn(RIGHT);
    }
